[0.001, "o", "      3/9 - Met with Kimball and documented some requirements for the sandbox environment. Requested a POC and am working on creating functional\r\n      assets, with some possible configuration needed from the POC team.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n  \u001b[2m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[1m\u001b[36mSuzi Rodriguez\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m•\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m2026-02-27\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m14d ago\u001b[0m  \u001b[1m\u001b[33m NINJA UPDATE \u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "      2/27 - \u001b[1m\u001b[32m@Christopher Kleemann\u001b[0m met with Kimball Crocket in person and had a productive conversation about the continued selection process and our\r\n      leading position to meet their functional needs over Oracle (last competitor in play). Kimball has also asked for a sandbox environment.\r\n      Investigating best path forward with a likely replica of the Distribution partition as an option for Kimball to play with and give us his final\r\n      stamp of approval.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "      Kimball also mentioned that the EMEA team needs to see a demo of their processes mapped into Pricefx to get them on board and seeing a future\r\n      in the platform. Thus far I was preparing for a US demo which has very different use cases. Pivoting to preparing the EMEA demo asap. Not\r\n      scheduled yet but Kimball asked for the demo the week of 3/2.\r\n      (NINJA UPDATE)\r\n\r\n"]
