[0.000, "o", "      \u001b[1m\u001b[32m@Suzi Rodriguez\u001b[0m, \u001b[1m\u001b[32m@Todd Carlton\u001b[0m, \u001b[1m\u001b[32m@Christopher Kleemann\u001b[0m, and myself gave a 2nd demo to Southco, focused on core Price Setting & Agreements\r\n      functionality, as they had requested. The demo was well-received and they specifically called out how it was much more in line with what they\r\n      wanted to see in terms of near-term functionality and goals. They were very engaged, asking questions, posing scenarios, and playing out\r\n      timelines of what an implementation with PFX would look like. They asked for some information on the types of data we would need for an\r\n      implementation, which I will provide.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "      There is one other pricing solution they're looking at, but we now seem very well-positioned to move forward with Agents + Price Setting in the\r\n      near term as they approach their August deadline for having a pricing management solution in place.\r\n      CC: \u001b[1m\u001b[32m@Jose Paez\u001b[0m, \u001b[1m\u001b[32m@Tim Chilson\u001b[0m\r\n      NINJA UPDATE\r\n\r\n\r\n  \u001b[2mPress Enter to go back...\u001b[0m"]
