[1.180, "o", "\r\n  \u001b[1m\u001b[35m── Chatter ──\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[1m\u001b[36mMeredith Campbell\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m•\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m2026-03-06\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m7d ago\u001b[0m  \u001b[1m\u001b[33m NINJA UPDATE \u001b[0m\r\n\r\n      Led three joint working sessions with Avery Dennison stakeholders to clarify data requirements and deployment approach, coordinating with\r\n      Antoine on the agents he had already built and reviewed with AD. Designed new agents (a Cost Pass‑Through Effectiveness Tracker and a\r\n      below‑list‑price uplift agent) and aligned on including the Agent Assessment dashboard, moving the AD NA Agents pilot toward concrete build and\r\n      validation. Trained Sanjeev on how to create and configure agents so he can independently test and iterate.\r\n      Identified an integration opportunity with the customer's existing Google Looker analytics stack and flagged it to Product/Engineering (via\r\n      Madhav) to explore Model Context Protocol (MCP) connections. This would allow agents to surface only truly actionable insights by filtering out\r\n      cases with documented business justifications in"]
[0.000, "o", " quote records (for example, intentional price decreases that don't need to be\r\n      re‑investigated). This approach addresses stakeholder feedback, particularly from Kathleen Flagg, to focus agents on Pricefx‑specific data\r\n      rather than duplicating existing BI capabilities.\r\n      (NINJA UPDATE) \u001b[1m\u001b[32m@Jose Paez\u001b[0m \u001b[1m\u001b[32m@Madhav Kuruppath\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\r\n  \u001b[2mPress Enter to go back...\u001b[0m"]
